RiakLight is a Riak binding that doesn't require ActiveRecord or too many
crazy ruby gems.  It does require that you install 'libruby-json' and
also 'gem install curb'.   Then you should be good to go.  

More features should be added over time.

Example:

riak = RiakLight.new()
puts riak.bucket_info("llamas").inspect()
puts riak.bucket_add("llamas", "bob", { "says" => "I'm not a llama" }).inspect()
puts riak.bucket_get("llamas", "bob").inspect()
puts riak.bucket_get("llamas", "steve").inspect()

Q&A?

